Protesters blocking traffic at LAX
Protesters opposing President Trump's travel ban block World Way at Los Angeles International Airport.

Marzieh Moosavizadeh reunited with her grandson at LAX after being detained for 9 hours. She had no idea whether she would be released or sent back. Finally, at 1 a.m., she was released.   

Speaking in Persian and translated by her son, she had a message for the president: 

"Please, tell Mr. Trump when they make these kind of decisions, think it all the way through." 

Read her full story: http://lat.ms/2khnjYo
